The paper deals with network analysis and centrality measures, which are commonly studied in the subfield of social network analysis (cs.SI) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the behavior of these measures as parameters vary, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The concept of walk classes and their impact on centrality measures is related to spectral graph theory (cs.SD), and the paper also discusses the use of matrix-based centrality measures, which is a topic in linear algebra (cs.LG).
